[thinking] I’m looking at how the generated class works, and I think the className matches, which is good. But if dynamic access reports map classes loaded from the test output, that needs to be included. It could be related to the SourceFile. I'm suspecting that the class loader picks the original jar before the test classes. Gradle generally loads test classes first, but I wonder about the impact if TCK uses an effective jar with -javaagent. I also need to consider class resolution and potential issues with the loading order.
