[thinking] 
[thinking] I noticed that the closure is referenced by the constant pool when the cookies method is invoked, leading the classloader to load that closure. I should check if the generated output includes the closure override. It might be useful to enhance the test to assert that the class resource comes from the build/classes, but I’m not entirely convinced that’s necessary. I’m also thinking that a NoSuchMethodError could arise if response.getCookies() calls a package-private closure constructor. If both classes are from the same loader, we’re probably fine, but Java modules might complicate things.
