[thinking] 
[thinking] I realized that the Closure might set maximumNumberOfParameters through reflection, which could help with managing Java subclasses when finding doCall methods. I’m considering including a direct method in the test after responseWithCookie().getCookies(), but maybe that isn't necessary since it currently calls the class twice. I’m also wondering if I should change direct access to avoid catching LinkageError around responseWithCookie().getCookies() because if native Groovy initialization fails, we wouldn't cover that well. We’d just get a report from the JVM instead.
